                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">QB1 (cheap improvement to AR cast time - stacks with items / spells)
<br />
SCM3 (mana conservation)
<br />

<br />
after that, it's your call as to order...
<br />

<br />
TD3 (longer charm duration)
<br />
QB3 (to get AR down to 2.5 unbuffed)
<br />
CA3 / LR5 (to avoid getting hit)
<br />
GM (to go from 0 mana to FM in bad sit or after rez)
<br />
Perm Illusion (perma-scaled wolf - greater wolf form if you have a drood partner)
<br />
ND3
<br />

<br />
Now, CF is somewhat debatable.  It was an AA I thought worked when I trained level 1.  Level 2 and 3 I got no perceived improvement.  I say perceived, because I have no data to prove otherwise.  There must be something to it though, or many high end guilds with AA requirements wouldn't be looking for it.
<br />

<br />
After you have all those, I would start mez mastery (WoM, Tash, Recharm).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
