                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There are two methods to charm in the god trials.  The first is to stand far behind the group and when charm breaks, mez the mob and then recharm after it been snared again.  This  method is low risk, to the enchanter and does not take a lot of AA's and gear for you to be good at it.
<br />

<br />
The second method is to stand close to the group and when charm breaks wait till the mob starts hitting you to cast wom, then recharm.  This method works very well as well, but it needs an enchanter with good gear a lot of experience and a huge amount of AA's
<br />

<br />
Only in a few of the god zones will you be charming, so there is no need to spend a lot of AA's for just a few zones.    Finish off spell casting subtley 3,  with gear or AA's get your casting time of arcane to 50 percent, then start working on LR5.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
