                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I generally use WoM to get my Pooka under control, I am time geared buffed with around 7600 hps usually with 460ish AA.  WoM is wonderful but even more wonderful is Snare, backup bard mez or a nice pally/wiz/cleric Stun.  If you have a slow puller it's not always possible to get enough room for an unsnared pet, so tight quarters are sometimes needed.
<br />

<br />
Back to the general question. I prefer the defensive AA's for charming after getting TD maxxed.  Helps you survive, because Murphy's Law says that charm is going to break occasionally at the worst time - no heals, no snares, no stuns - Higher Charisma will help you if you have enough space to try and channel a few hits but plain just being able to live thru the hits will help a lot more.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />66.001/Pr h-- 5.4Khp 6.9Km FT15 G++++! E+++++ T++ L+ F B C++++ T++++</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
